# Approach
    Use selection(reverse) sort algorithm and swap the row having highest value at kth column with row having low value.

# Complexity
- Time complexity: O(n ^ 2)
>

# Code
```
class Solution {
    public int[][] sortTheStudents(int[][] score, int k) {
        for(int i=0;i<score.length;i++){
            int index = i;
            for(int j = i+1; j < score.length;j++){
                if(score[j][k] > score[index][k]){
                    index = j;
                }
            }
            swapArray(score,index,i);
        }
            return score;
    }

    private void swapArray(int[][] arr,int from,int to){
        for(int i = 0;i<arr[0].length;i++){
            int temp = arr[from][i];
            arr[from][i] = arr[to][i];
            arr[to][i] = temp;
        }
    }
}
```

