# Approach
- Create a PriorityQueue and pass a pair storing the array and its kth index value.
- Pass all the array elements to the priority queue.
- poll each element and store them in the list and finally convert the list to array. 

# Code
```
class Solution {
    class Pair{
        int[] arr;
        int val;
        public Pair(int[] arr, int val){
            this.arr=arr;
            this.val=val;
        }
    }
    public int[][] sortTheStudents(int[][] score, int k) {
        ArrayList<int[]> ans = new ArrayList<>();
        // int size = score[0].length;
        PriorityQueue<Pair> heap = new PriorityQueue<>((a,b)->(b.val - a.val));
        for(int[] arr: score){
            Pair p = new Pair(arr, arr[k]);
            heap.offer(p);
        }
        while(!heap.isEmpty()){
            Pair rem =heap.poll();
            int[] array = rem.arr;
            ans.add(array);
        }
        return ans.toArray(new int[ans.size()][]);
    }
}
```

