# Intuition
Use the map to store the indexes of the matrix of "k" exam marks in decreasing order. 
# Approach
put the map to store the indexes of the matrix of "k" exam marks in decreasing order. Then iterate the map and store the rows to the final result.
# Complexity
- Time complexity:
O(n)

- Space complexity:
O(n)
# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    vector<vector<int>> sortTheStudents(vector<vector<int>>& score, int k) {
        std::map<int, int, greater<int> > markToStudentsMap; 
        int idx=0;
        vector<vector<int>> result(score.size());

        while(idx<score.size())
        {
            markToStudentsMap[score[idx][k]] = idx;
            idx++;
        }
        idx=0;
        for(auto itr : markToStudentsMap) {
            result[idx] = score[itr.second];
            idx++;
        }
        return result;
    }   
};
```

